Java Control statements:
   This decides how the program flow.
   1. which Code runs.
   2. how many times it runs or i have a piece of code that should run multiple times
   3. under what conditions it runs.

1. Decision Making statement
    These statements decide which block of code should run based on a condition.
   1. If statement - Runs code only if codition is true 
       if(condition){
          //code to executec
       }
   2. if else statement
       choose between 2 blocks of code.
       if(condition){
        //Code to execute when condition satisfies
       }else{
          //Code to execute when condition is not satisfied
       }
   3. if else if ladder
       used when there are multiple conditions
       if(condtion1){
         // code to execute
       } else if(condition){
        //code to execute
       } else if(condition){
        //code to execute
       }else{
        //code to execute
       }

   4. switch statement.
      used when checking multiple values of one variable.

      if(num == 1){
         //code to execute if value is 1
      }else if(num == 2){
        //code to execute if value is 2
      } else if(num == 3) {
        //code to execute if value is 3
      }else{
        //code to execute if none of value in case is matching 
      }


      Syntax:
        int num = 3;
          switch(num){
            case 1:
                //code to execute if value is 1
                break;
            case 2:
                //code to execute if value is 2
                break;
            case 3:
                //code to execute if value is 3
                break;
            default:
               //code to execute if none of value in case is matching  
          }


2. Looping statements
  Loops are used when we want to repeat code multiple times.
1. For Loop
   The for loop is used when we know how many times the loop should run.
   syntax:
      for(initialization, condition, increment/decrement){
        //bock of code that has to be repeated.
      }
    initialization - we take a variable and assign a default value.
    condition - It will be evaluated to true or false.
    increment/decrement - var++/var--
   
 Steps:
    1. initialization
    2. after initialiazation goes to condition and checks.
    3. if condition satisifies executes block of code.
    4. goto inc/dec value will increment or decrement.  
    5. goto condition.
    6. if true executes block of code else come out of loop.

2. while loop
   This is used to repeat a block of code whie a condtion is true.(Zero or more times.)
  Syntax:
     while(condition){
      //block of code.
     }

    Steps:
    1. The condition is cheked first.
    2. when the condition is true block of code executes
    3. After executing block of code again checks for condition.
    4. Loop stops when condition is false. 

3. do while loop
    This is used to repeat a block of code atleast one time. (1 or more times)
  do{
      // Block of code
  }while(condition);  
  
   Steps:
      1. Execute code inside do.
      2. check condition
      3. if condition true - repeat.
      4. if condition false - stop.


3. Jump statements.

   These statements are used to transfer control from one part to another part.

   1. break - Stops the loop immediately and transfer control to outside of loop.
   Ex: for(int i=0; i <=10; i++){
           if(i == 5){
               break;
           }
           System.out.println(i);
       }
   
   2. continue - Skips the current iteration
   ex: for(int i=0; i <=10; i++){
            if(i == 5){
                continue;
            }
            System.out.println("ayiyiuyiyui"+i);
            System.out.println(i);
            System.out.println("sdsdasdasd"+i);
        }
        print of 5 will be skipped.
        oup - 1 2 3 4 6 7 8 9 10
   3. return
     return - stops the program and return control to the caller.
       loop stops
       entire metod stops
       no code executes after return.

